OL,3,CLiverpool hotel owners have say on
OL,4,Cwhether to introduce tourist levy on
OL,5,Crooms
OL,7,FThe levy idea is masterminded and
OL,8,Fmanaged by Liverpool's Accommodation
OL,9,FBusiness Improvement District which
OL,10,Fsays it will plough the #6m income
OL,11,Finto the city's visitor economy,
OL,12,Fpublic realm and events calendar.
OL,14,FIf the ballot is passed the levy would
OL,15,Fapply only in city centre hotels which
OL,16,Fare part of Liverpool's Accommodation
OL,17,FBusiness Improvement District (ABID).
OL,19,FThe results of the vote are due to be
OL,20,Fannounced on 24 April and the charge
OL,21,Fcould be in place by June.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/7
